reviews.text: I love taking my dog there she has so much fun.
Lots of info about the coast and areas to visit. Great trails, easily navigable for all abilities.
Next to the parking lot is a little path that wanders through the trees.  It's so magical to come out of the woodsy path and onto the beach.
Really nice spot to stop! Easy beach access and loads of information. Nice bathrooms too! Brand new facility.

Love it here! It's like driftwood heaven, it's everywhere!! Did not get a chance to go in visitor center, but will definitely take time to stop inside next time I get to Brookings, which I hope is soon. Beach is serene and uncrowded, once you climb over the driftwood, it's a great place to take a walk along the beach and pick up some cool little stone and wood treasures.

Relaxed dining, comfort food well prepared. Friendly efficient staff. Choice of grilled or beer battered cod for fish and chips. Full bar.
 View of small boat harbor. Outside dining available. Delicious fajitas.

What a wonderful restaurant! We decided to eat outside and my husband thought it was too cold, so they brought us two blankets & an outdoor heater! The food was awesome, very fresh, and the service was great. The owners are very friendly and Peggy, thank you!

Beautiful spot on the harbor. The staff is friendly and the food was good. The owner is a sweetheart. I mentioned her beautiful succulents and she broke off pieces for my friends and I to start our own. (She obviously can't do that for everyone);; it made our day.
Clam chowder bread bowls are made from scratch and super yummy. The place is dated and could use a face lift. Staff was not very attentive. Still one of my favorite places to get seafood.
So great! The owner even came out to shake our hand. The award winning Clam chowder definitely lived up to it's name! Highly recommend!

A beautiful historical landmark that I feel privileged to have toured. Offshore Lighthouses are expensive to maintain and frankly on the west coast, rare to tour. You take a helicopter from Crescent City airport 7 mi. Out to sea, Land and tour from the lantern room to basement. Once a month Nov-May. $300 pp. The money helps to restore it. For Lighthouse passport owners, there is a stamp in the kitchen. stgeorgereeflighthouse.us

A few years back I went on a tour of the light house. Some local people are restoring this light house and fly you out in a helicopter, land on it , Drop you off and return to Crescent City. Now you are 6-7 miles off shore to start your tour of a 160 ' high I think built in 1880's out of large granet block's . The lighthouse is a PC.of art and the tour is something everybody should see. Most people will never even  see it becauce it's so far out from shore. If you ever get a chance don't miss it. Thanks
NRHP reference number 93001373
this is not a bridge

My first time at your restaurant I was by myself and had prompt friendly service and some of the best French toast I've had. My second visit was the next day this time with my husband. Though it was a busy Saturday morning the waitress from the previous day recognized me. She was so friendly and took our orders and we received our awesome food in record time. This place is well deserving of 5 stars.
Nice restaurant, plenty of natural lighting. Friendly atmosphere. Senior menu has few but very good offerings. We ate there twice and always left happy. Great waffles!

Mattie's is the most amazing breakfast spot in Brookings,  there staff is so friendly and helpful.  There food is absolutely delicious, pancakes are so fully and there omelets are perfect! I love this place and recommend it to everyone to come to this very cute and quaint spot!!
Legendary. Local favorite. Food to die for. Light, fluffy, never gluey, always fresh. Cannot be beat. Enjoy!
Fast service and great food. A bustling and friendly place. Love that there was a GF option for toast.

This was our second time to this location and love the food. We go to this restaurant every time we are in town. The sushi is fresh and portions are great for the price. The atmosphere is perfect and they do have a bar to sit at for convenience. Service was great and staff very helpful with selections.   We will definitely visit this restaurant again when back in town.

The sushi was good I tried the smoked salmon and one other thing, it's been a week since I've gone there, the wait wasn't bad, it had a good turnout the night my sister, her husband and I went out. That waiter could have been in a better mood while serving us, otherwise I would have given them a five star. I wouldn't mind going back and trying something else off the menu, they have a good selection to choose from.

reviews.author_name: Web Services by Linda L Johnson
reviews.text: Happy Hour, 4-5pm only! Great food, drinks, and service thank you, Sarah! Best prices, quality, and quantity...great bang for your buck! Calamari with spicy dipping sauce was my favorite, $3; Spicy Avocado Crunch Roll, $3; California Roll, $3. Well drinks, $3; tap beer, $3. Only 4-5 pm, Happy Hour!!
The ramen was pretty good. Not the best I have ever had but a close second. The spicy tuna was excellent. The place was very busy but the service was still very good.

First time there. With Food allergies. Sydney was our server. She was Very understanding and helpful. 
 Food was very good. Services was very good. Prices fair. Nice atmosphere. Quite, not like a lot of other places in town. If no flair with food issue, will go back.
Great place with great staff. I go there at least once a week for the best burger or fish and chips in town.
However, they were closing permanently! Opening another restaurant in the Harbor area..Beach Front.
I love this place.  The burger is delicious and so are the veggies!
Very good service and excellent food at a reasonable price
Gourmet food at reasonable prices. Beautiful restaurant & lounge. Very relaxing & romantic.

I was pleasantly surprised how good the food is here! It is a modest store front but don't let it fool you! The pizza is great, you can taste the freshness. Sooo much better than the big chain companies. The pasta was amazing! 12$ and you get a giant serving, enough for four bowls of pasta with garlic knots and a side salad. Highly recommend the napoletana linguine. Service was great too. They went out of their way to provide extra napkins and side of ranch.

Based on online reviews and its close proximity to my hotel, I ordered delivery during my stay in Ann Arbor.  I ordered a half Greek salad and an Italian sausage pizza.  The salad was pure perfection!  I highly recommend it.  The pizza was also very good (I enjoyed leftovers the next day, too).  I took off one star because the delivery didn't include napkins or utensils.  I mean, I'm staying in a hotel--do you really expect me to have these things readily on hand?  I had to go down to the front desk and request a plastic fork so I could eat my salad.  You guys have great food, so please don't forget the little things that travelers in hotels need.  :)

Just get pizza from this place. Chicken or Pasta is waste of money. Pizza is the best. Do not dine in. Order to go. Bathroom is horrible. They have cleaning problem. The lady who run the place trying her best she is nice. But they need to spend money on the place.

I don't know how this place has so many good reviews. I tried them for the first time last night and will not return. I stopped in for carryout pizza by the slice for my boyfriend and me. First of all, the layout of the restaurant is dysfunctional. The kitchen/working area is so small, I don't know how the three employees were able to move around. And that's another thing. The floor behind the counter has plastic pallets on it and the employees were walking around on the pallets. It was one of the strangest things I've ever seen in a pizza place. The cash register is on a small counter where other customers were just standing around waiting for their orders, so it was impossible to try to place my order and pay. After forcing my way to the register, I ordered two cheese and two pepperoni slices. The cashier could barely figure out how to price them. Cheese and pepperoni are the most basic thing you can order! There were two other customers waiting for their orders and the staff was clearly confused who was supposed to get what order. The employees were running around manically and acting like they could barely comprehend what was going on in the store with three customers! I also noticed there was no hand washing going on as food was being handled. No employee had a clear designated spot to work. They were all just doing whatever. Who manages like that? When I finally received my order they only gave me three slices. I repeated my order of two cheese and two pepperoni. A few minutes later I received my order in a small box and thought to myself "how in the world are there four slices of New York style pizza in here? Did the employee stack them on top of each other?" I was so annoyed I walked out to my car, opened the box, and guess what? Three slices of pizza stacked on top of each other. Unbelievable is all I could think. And who stacks pizza on top of each other? I walked back in and told them my order was still wrong.  A different employee took a slice of cheese pizza, threw some pepperoni on top, and put it in the oven. This is weird, right? Then she pulled it out of the oven and told me to have a great night in an extremely phony voice. She didn't even apologize for the poor service. When I was a teenager, I worked at Cottage Inn, a restaurant with a very large menu and variety of items. I could run the register, take orders, and make all the food by myself on a busy night. It might be hard, but I could certainly handle it on my own. This place can't even get pizza by the slice right with two attempts and three employees working. I was extremely embarrassed for them and would hate to see what it's like when they're actually busy. The pizza was mediocre. Try at your own risk!

My husband liked their pizza a lot and ordered from them dozens of times we recently moved and are now 4 miles away if you view the longest google map route. We have had them deliver before as the route max time also shows as 9 minutes after placing our order and waiting over 30 minutes we received a call back saying we are too far and they will not deliver to us, this woman is the same rude woman we have spoken to before. We were told it would be arriving in 45 minutes when we placed our order and gave our address and he took our payment information as usual. The correct thing to do would have been to call and apologize call back explain they would still deliver our order but in the future they will no longer deliver. She also stated we are over 6 miles away which is not true no matter what route you take. She said it's just too far and did not offer any apology. This is very expensive for what you get- we are dissapointes with our experience and would not recommend this and will be going to many of the other 50 pizza options instead from now on.

The pizza was very good. Good portions for price, great service and very clean establishment.   They also have one pinball machine we loved. Would definitely go back. Potato chip portion great for the price.

Arrived at about 2:45 PM. First time here. When I ordered our pizza, the cashier asked for my customer card number. I told her no, never been here before. Didn't offer to sign us up. Took our order and told us our pick up number. We went to sit down and there were 2 big tables that hadn't been cleared of the previous diners lunch. We sat and waited for our pizza and mess was left there, when there was plenty of help to deal with it and they weren't busy. They called our number and we got our pizza. It was cut into small 3"  square pieces.... weird. The toppings were good but the crust was very thin. We also had to go searching for plates. They finally cleared the tables next to us about 40 minutes after we'd been there. We probably won't go back.

We come here every time we visit gold back and Brookings.  The best food and the place is beautiful over looking the bay. Nice warm atmosphere great for kids and families.  They have incredible food! The menu is more then pizza, salads, sandwiches all sorts of options.

A must have when you visit the coast

Nothing like the medford or Grant's pass versions. Staff ignores you while you're at the counter, dark and dirty dining area. Front entryway is beautiful and so is the building but the service was not what was expected, nor was the food. Our pizza was pretty good but missing items that were supposed to be on it, like artichokes and sun dried tomatoes.

This is a fantastic place!   Great food,  their own beer,  and an arcade for the kiddos. ..and those of us a bit older.   They have room for parties (you can reserve), and many screens.   Lots of sports to see.   Check it out! !
